In response, the Shanghai Stock Exchange on the evening of February 23 to oriental biology issued a regulatory inquiry letter, requiring the company to explain the new coronavirus diagnostic series of products in the European Union registration of specific progress; Whether domestic sales require approval or permission from the Authority; whether there is a dispute or potential dispute over the ownership of the product; such as domestic sales, impact on current operations and performance.

The company completed the development of a new COVID-19(2019-nCoV) series test reagent in early February, according to a February 23 announcement by Orient biosciences. The range of products includes colloidal gold-based immunochromatography for the rapid detection of Covid-192019-ncov and fluorescent PCR platform for the detection of Covid-192019-ncov.

On the evening of February 27, the company issued a response letter to a regulatory inquiry from the Shanghai Stock Exchange, stating that the European Union Ce Standard Certification for the company's new coronavirus diagnostic series would be completed after a declaration of conformity and submission to the competent European Union authorities, that can be sold.

In terms of performance impact, according to the company's current hand orders, oriental biology believes that the EU sales of related products have no significant impact on the company's current operations and performance; Because of the uncertainty over whether the company's COVID-19 products would qualify for a medical device registration certificate, the company does not believe that domestic sales of the products would have a significant impact on its current operations and performance. In addition, oriental biology believes that there is no patent dispute over the new coronavirus diagnostic series.

In response to the disclosure on the same day of two announcements with contradictory information, the company claimed that due to time constraints, the company's board secretary made an operational error in uploading the announcement, uploading a valid version of the non-company approval procedure to the announcement system in error, resulting in errors in the clarification notice as to whether the company is currently able to sell in the European Union and whether it is primarily selling overseas, relevant information does not accurately reflect the actual situation of the company. At present, the company has launched an internal accountability mechanism to investigate the responsibility of those responsible.

The interface journalist called oriental biology on issues such as the initial production scale of the new coronavirus diagnostic series products. An internal staff member of the company told the interface journalist, the initial production can not be estimated because the relevant products have not yet been approved or licensed in the domestic market. As for the EU market, the total amount of EU customer orders currently in the hands of the company is about US $30,000, follow-up companies will be based on different customer needs, continue to adjust the production scale of different types of products.

"New coronavirus diagnostic series of related products production and marketing, the company is still based on the development of the epidemic to judge. Originally thought that there will be considerable market demand in the domestic market, the research and development completed in early February, but the approval process is not yet finished, the result of the EU market filing soon passed. So it's still hard to tell,"the official said.

According to the Prospectus, the company mainly provides in vitro diagnostic reagents to overseas medical device distributors, and its revenue from overseas sales is the main source of the company's revenue, accounting for more than 94% of the total revenue for a long time.

The prospectus shows that in 2017,2018 and the first three quarters of 2019, the total revenue achieved by oriental biology was 224 million yuan, 286 million yuan and 262 million yuan respectively; The net profit attributable to the shareholders of the parent company was 33 million yuan, 64 million yuan and 58 million yuan respectively.
